2006-12-20 00:42  dangelo

	* src/Panorama/Panorama.cpp, src/common/Makefile.am,
	  src/common/eig_jacobi.cpp, src/hugin/AssistantPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin/PreviewFrame.cpp, src/hugin/PreviewPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin/xrc/data/straighten_pano.xpm,
	  src/hugin/xrc/preview_frame.xrc, src/include/PT/PanoCommand.h,
	  src/include/common/Matrix3.h, src/include/common/Vector3.h,
	  src/include/common/eig_jacobi.h,
	  src/include/hugin/PreviewFrame.h: Added "Straighten" button to
	  automatically straigten wavy horizons.
	  Idea based on Matthew Brown's IJCV article.
	  Current does not work with images that were taken in portrait
	  mode,
	  but physically still stored in landscape format.

